STEP 1 — Create AWS Foundation

Do only this step first.

1. Create AWS Account

If not already done:

Create AWS account
Enable MFA on root account

2. Create IAM Admin User

AWS Console

IAM
 → Users
 → Create User

Create:

streamvault-admin

Attach:

AdministratorAccess

Login using this user from now on.

Never use root account.

3. Create Budget Alert
Billing
 → Budgets

Create:

Monthly Budget = $10

Email notifications:

80%
100%

This prevents accidental charges.

4. Choose AWS Region

Use:

ap-south-1 (Mumbai)

Keep every service in this region.

5. Create GitHub Repository

Create:

streamvault

Push:

Clo/

into GitHub.

6. Verify Project Runs Locally

Inside:

cd streamvault

npm install

npm run dev

Open:

http://localhost:3000

Confirm:

Login page works
Register page works
No Prisma errors
Stop Here

Once you've completed Step 1 and confirmed:

AWS account ready
IAM user created
Budget configured
GitHub repo created
Next.js app runs locally
